---
title: "How to Know When Your Business Has Outgrown Off-the-Shelf Software"
date: "2023-08-01"
summary: "Know when your business has outgrown off-the-shelf software. The signs are visible if you look."
coverImage: ""
tags:
  - "Business Strategy"
author: "Redevise"
---

Your off-the-shelf software worked when you bought it. It does not work now. The business has outgrown it. The software is holding you back.

Here are the signs.

Workarounds exceed 20 percent of [workflows](/process). If more than 20 percent of your work happens outside the software, the software is not serving you.

Data is manually reconciled across systems. If someone is copying data between your software and other systems every week, the software is not integrated.

Reporting requires manual compilation. If a report requires data from your software and other systems and manual compilation, the software is not enough.

New features are requested constantly. If you are always requesting features that do not exist, the software is not built for your business.

I evaluated a client's software in 2024. The workarounds were 35 percent of [workflows](/process). The data was manually reconciled. The reporting was manually compiled. The feature requests were constant. The software was the constraint.

We built [custom software](/services#software). The workarounds dropped to 8 percent. The reconciliation was automated. The reporting was automated. The feature requests dropped.

The teams that do not recognize the signs are the ones staying on software that constrains them. The teams that recognize are the ones moving to software that serves them.

Measure the workarounds. Check the reconciliation. Check the reporting. Check the feature requests. If the signs are present, you have outgrown the software.
